<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>BUSINESS</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/03/business/03ENRO.html?todaysheadlines">Enron Panel Finds Inflated Profits and Few Controls</a></b><br>
In a report released Saturday night, a special committee of Enron's board said that the company had falsely inflated its profits by almost $1 billion last year.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/03/business/yourmoney/03CONG.html?todaysheadlines">Enron Scandal Shocks Even Those  
Who Helped It Along</a></b><br>
Some of the lawmakers and regulators investigating some of the causes behind the Enron-Arthur Andersen scandal may need to look no further than a mirror.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/03/business/yourmoney/03OPTI.html?todaysheadlines">Even Last Year, Option Spigot Was Wide Open</a></b><br>
As corporate earnings and cash flow have ebbed and stock prices have fallen, boards have been doling out options as a cheap, balance-sheet-friendly way of compensating managers.
<P>
</font>













<p>
<a href="http://www.nytimes.com/pages/business/index.html?todaysheadline">MORE BUSINESS NEWS</a>
