<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>POLITICS</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/03/politics/03GORE.html?todaysheadlines">Gore Rebukes Bush, and Tries to Mend Fences at Home in Tennessee</a></b><br>
Al Gore re-emerged in his home state, criticizing President Bush's policies on several domestic issues.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/03/international/americas/03CUBA.html?todaysheadlines">Bush Hires Hard-Liners to Handle Cuba Policy</a></b><br>
The Bush administration is filling its Latin America policy ranks with officials known for a hard-line stance toward Fidel Castro's government.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/03/politics/03BUDG.html?todaysheadlines">Bush Budget Links Dollars to Deeds With New Ratings</a></b><br>
President Bush's proposed budget plan will for the first time formally assess the performance of government agencies and link their financing to the grades they receive.
<P>
</font>













<p>
<a href="http://www.nytimes.com/pages/politics/index.html?todaysheadline">MORE POLITICS NEWS</a>
