<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>ARTS</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/03/arts/03OSCA.html?todaysheadlines">What Price Buzz? Hollywood Breaks Bank for Oscar Race</a></b><br>
Hollywood studios are in the middle of the   biggest Oscar spending spree in history.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/03/arts/television/03RIDI.html?todaysheadlines">What Price Success for a Newly Popular BBC?</a></b><br>
The BBC beat its main rival, ITV, in the 2001 ratings race. The hallowed institution now finds itself being accused of having lowered its standards.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/03/movies/03HOHE.html?todaysheadlines">For Frances's Youth, 'un Teen Movie'</a></b><br>
French filmmakers have newly taken on a staple of American culture  the teen movie  and its raw  treatment of teenage sexuality.
<P>
</font>













